    {
      "id": "6b7ddcc3_b60c1b9f",
      "file_path": "vid-app-common/src/main/java/org/onap/vid/aai/AaiOverTLSClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 107,
      "message": "I see here two issues.\nI do NOT think these should block this commit (or be part of), but still should be addressed:\n\n1. From generalization perspective, it should be good to have the request info in the return value.\n   e.g. Extending HttpResponse model.\n   Same applies for the exceptions: if can throw ExceptionWithRequestInfo, this is much better, in my view.\n\n2. `syncRestClient.get` has a fallback mechanism -- `callWithRetryOverHttp`. In case of probing, we will lose the indication of root case when `causedBySslHandshakeError` is positive. I think it's an important information we _should_ give somehow.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4379,
        "name": "Ittay Stern",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ittay.stern@att.com",
        "username": "ittays"
      },
      "updated": "2019-06-17 08:27:15.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "f24bb2f9_7f4af6e0",
      "file_path": "vid-app-common/src/main/java/org/onap/vid/aai/AaiOverTLSClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 109,
      "message": "I suggest leaking the whole URI, including host, port, protocol. i.e. `urlBase + String.format(URIS.SUBSCRIBERS, 0)`.\nThis will assist understanding misconfigs.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4379,
        "name": "Ittay Stern",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ittay.stern@att.com",
        "username": "ittays"
      },
      "updated": "2019-06-17 08:27:15.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
